name: site
summary: "The known.life genepool itself вЂ” an Astro SSR app on a Cloudflare Worker that IS the registry (publish В· resolve В· auth В· scan В· gene viewer) plus the docs site. This is the one production surface every other .life depends on: install.sh is served from here, /api/resolve/<gene>/latest is how genes are inherited, and the engine ships as the `life` package's files[\"life\"]. Deploys under the convention as a ci-auto unit (it's production, default-on); the live Cloudflare resources predate the convention, so config: pins their names and binding vars (env.KNOWN_KV / env.KNOWN_R2) rather than refactoring the worker. The deploy is THIS repo's own вЂ” the canonical dogfood worst case the ci-deploy-convention was designed against."

requires:
  - infra.compute
  - infra.route
  - infra.datastore
  - infra.kv
  - infra.object_store
  - infra.secret_store
  # Workers AI (env.AI) вЂ” query/summary embeddings for semantic /search
  # (lib/semantic.ts); the worker fails open to lexical search without it.
  - infra.ai

# The registry CORE вЂ” the load-bearing capability every .life boots through
# (resolve В· publish В· auth В· scan В· lifecycle В· the D1/R2/KV/AI data path) вЂ” lives
# ONLY in the pool as the known.life/registry gene (floating latest). It is NOT in
# this repo in any form: `imports:` materializes it into `.genome/registry/`
# (gitignored, rehydrated per environment by `life inherit`, the same way any
# imported gene materializes into `.genome/<gene>/`), and `src/middleware.ts` imports
# `registryFetch` from there. Edit the gene (`life fetch registry` в†’ mutate); the
# next evolve floats to it. The NON-load-bearing surfaces (homepage, /docs,
# marketing, static assets) stay Astro in this repo вЂ” a website, not infra.
imports:
  - known.life/registry
  # The multi-life viewer (served at /app) вЂ” same ownership cut as the
  # registry: the gene is the sole source, materialized into .genome/viewer/
  # and mounted from src/middleware.ts; this repo holds no copy.
  - known.life/viewer

# Deploy to the live Worker script name, not the unit's (`site`). Per-resource
# names + binding vars are pinned to the resources that predate the convention
# (the worker reads env.KNOWN_KV / env.KNOWN_R2 / env.DB), so `life deploy`
# binds the existing stores instead of provisioning fresh empty ones.
deploy_name: known-life
config:
  db_name: known-life-db
  kv_title: known-life-known_kv
  kv_binding: KNOWN_KV
  bucket: known-life-known-r2
  r2_binding: KNOWN_R2

# Build: install deps, fold the root installer into the served assets (it's
# served at known.life/install.sh from the gene pool, not raw GitHub), then run
# the Astro Cloudflare build в†’ dist/_worker.js (SSR module graph) + dist/ assets.
build: npm ci --no-audit --no-fund && cp ../install.sh public/install.sh && npm run build

# The build above embeds the repo-root installer, so an install.sh edit must
# trigger this unit's ci-auto deploy (engine в‰Ґ3.46.0 deploy_inputs) вЂ” without
# it, an installer change "deploys" as a silent no-op until the next site/ touch.
deploy_inputs:
  - install.sh
  # The lockfile: this unit's worker IS mostly vendored genes (registry, viewer
  # вЂ” materialized from these pins at CI), so a lock-only re-pin is a real code
  # change here. Without this, a gene patch published + re-pinned ships as a
  # silent no-op deploy (lived 2026-07-18: registry@0.8.1's /jwks fix sat
  # unshipped behind a green "deploy: skipped").
  - .life.lock
artifact: dist/_worker.js
assets:
  dir: ./dist
  binding: ASSETS
  not_found: 404-page

# A public site on the apex custom domain. It brings its own worker, so it
# authenticates its own privileged paths (owner-gate on publish/lifecycle, the
# /exchange boot flow) вЂ” there is no injected gate; `public: true` is the honest
# marker that the surface itself is world-reachable.
route: known.life
public: true

# Post-deploy smoke (engine в‰Ґ3.38.0): the genepool's two load-bearing surfaces
# answer after every CI deploy вЂ” the installer every cold-start curls, and the
# resolve endpoint every .life inherits through. A mismatch fails the deploy.
verify:
  - /install.sh=200
  - /api/resolve/life/latest=200
  # The multi-life viewer's sign-in page (src/viewer, mounted at /app).
  - /app=200

# Eyes on the one production surface every .life depends on (Law 13). `observe:`
# is the PORTABLE observability knob (cloudflare gene в‰Ґ1.36.8) вЂ” the adapter maps
# it to CF Workers Logs + Traces metadata. Read it back with `node scripts/
# observe.mjs`. Logs + traces share the Workers Logs free tier (200k events/day);
# `true` = full sampling (registry traffic is low, so well within it; use
# `observe: { sampling: N }` to dial down if volume ever climbs).
observe: true

# CF-runtime config with no portable meaning вЂ” the exact pinned compatibility
# the live worker runs on. nodejs_compat is required by the Astro CF adapter.
cloudflare:
  compatibility_date: "2026-05-01"
  compatibility_flags:
    - nodejs_compat

# The worker's security-spine unit suite вЂ” scan (the leak gate), lifekey-verify
# (the auth root), jwt (the write-endpoint bearer), db-accounts (the upsert behind
# /api/auth/prove). Pure WebCrypto/jose/node:sqlite, the one fetch stubbed, no
# network вЂ” a genuinely self-contained ARTIFACT test (the one the unified-CI
# `life test --changed` rail runs for site/, replacing the hand-kept worker-unit
# job). cwd is this dir, so no `cd site`.
tests:
  - npm ci && npm run test:coverage

---

# site вЂ” the known.life genepool

This directory is **the genepool itself**: the deployable that serves
[known.life](https://known.life). It plays two independent roles (see the root
`.life` and `CLAUDE.md`) вЂ” here it is purely the *deployment surface*; the rest
of the repo is a .life that happens to use the genepool this worker hosts.

## What it serves

An [Astro](https://astro.build) app with the Cloudflare adapter, deployed as a
single SSR Worker plus edge static assets:

- **The registry API** вЂ” the genepool's request-handling core (`publish` В·
  `resolve` В· `package` В· `claim` В· `lifecycle` В· `maintainers` В· `auth` В·
  `mcp` В· `setup` В· `github-app` В· `skill` В· the `/api/index` transparency
  index, mirrored into the public repo so registry history is append-only in
  a git log this worker can't rewrite), which lives in **the
  `known.life/registry` gene** (`imports:` above), materialized into
  `.genome/registry/` and imported by `src/middleware.ts` вЂ” the repo holds no
  copy; the gene is the sole source. Its credential-free vitest suite
  (`npm test`) lives in `site/test/`.
- **The docs site** (`src/pages`, `src/layouts`, `src/components`) вЂ” prerendered
  to static assets.
- **The multi-life viewer** (served at `/app`) вЂ” sign in with GitHub (through
  this worker's own OAuth bridge вЂ” no new secrets), open any life repo you can
  reach (sessions list + the Life tab, artifacts included), and scaffold new
  lives from the browser. Lives in **the `known.life/viewer` gene**
  (`imports:` above), materialized into `.genome/viewer/` and mounted as one
  `viewerFetch(request, config)` call from `src/middleware.ts` вЂ” the repo
  holds no copy; edit = fetch в†’ mutate в†’ re-vendor, exactly like the registry.
  Its credential-free vitest suite lives in `site/test/viewer-*.test.ts`.
- **The installer** вЂ” `install.sh` (repo root) is copied into `public/` at build
  time and served from `known.life/install.sh`, so cold-start never depends on
  raw GitHub. Because that file lives outside this directory, the frontmatter
  declares it under `deploy_inputs:` (engine в‰Ґ3.46.0) so an installer edit
  triggers this unit's ci-auto deploy вЂ” before that, change detection keyed on
  `site/**` alone and an installer change shipped as a silent no-op.
- **The engine** вЂ” shipped as the `life` package's `files["life"]`, served from
  `/api/resolve/life/latest` like any other module (no separate static asset).

## How it deploys

Under the **ci-deploy-convention**: a push that changes `site/**` deploys this
unit from CI via the engine's `deploy --changed`, never by hand from a session
(`life deploy` against the live genepool would break every other .life). The
frontmatter above is the whole deploy spec вЂ” the cloudflare adapter absorbs the
build, the Astro module-graph upload, the asset exclusion of `_worker.js`, the
D1 schema apply (`schema.sql`, idempotent), resource-ID resolution by name, and
secret-text carry-through on redeploy. The `config:` overrides bind the live
`known-life-*` resources the worker already reads.

Backing data: **D1** (`known-life-db` вЂ” accounts, names, packages, versions,
installs, deps, embeddings, `auth_challenge` (lifekey sign-in nonces вЂ” one row
per challenge, strongly consistent so concurrent sign-ins don't collide);
`schema.sql`), **KV** (`known-life-known_kv` вЂ” caches, rate limits, OAuth state),
**R2** (`known-life-known-r2` вЂ”
content-addressed package blobs), **Workers AI** (`env.AI` вЂ” bge-base
embeddings powering semantic `/search`, computed lazily and cached in the D1
`embeddings` table; `lib/semantic.ts`). Operator secrets (`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`,
the OAuth client pair) are set out of band via `data <dir> secret set` and
survive every redeploy.

Observability: the worker emits **Workers Logs + Traces** (declared in the
portable `observe:` knob above; one span per handler/fetch/KV/R2/D1
call). Read the telemetry back from the terminal вЂ” no dashboard вЂ” with
`node scripts/observe.mjs [--since 6h] [--errors] [--traces] [text]`, which
mints a short-lived token via the cloudflare gene and queries the telemetry API.

The deeper deploy mechanics вЂ” the capabilityв†’primitive map, `route:` gating, the
Workers REST flow вЂ” live in the `cloudflare` skill (`life ask cloudflare`).

